  "texts": [
    "• We demonstrate the enhanced capabilities of SMART-SLIC's, RAG-enhanced LLM system, which utilizes chain-of-thought prompting with LLM agents to proficiently address scientific questions.",
    "Recent methods for building RAG-assisted [6] chatbot applications rely on unstructured text stored in vector databases for question answering (QA) tasks [10].",
    "Although the integration of knowledge graphs (KGs) in AI systems is not novel [11], increasingly, researchers are leveraging them to improve LLM reasoning while simultaneously addressing the reliability issues discussed in Section I [12]- [14].",
    "Despite the benefits, integrating domain-specific knowledge into chatbots requires substantial effort.",
    "Here, we review the prior work for common chatbot designs, the integration of domain-knowledge in RAG pipelines, and the steps required for constructing KGs."
  ],
